    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-15T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="800"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d800">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1519: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fish</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-15T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 15, 1939—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>37. Referring to my telegram No. 35, the Arab delegates except those from
                    Palestine have submitted counterproposals to the British suggestions principally
                    with regard to the transition period brought here by the Egyptian Ambassador at
                    London. The Arab delegates expect Great Britain will either speedily agree or
                    publish Great Britain’s own plan without further discussions with the Jews. It
                    is reported here that while Malcolm MacDonald is anxious to satisfy at once the
                    Arabs in view of the international situation the British Foreign Office does not
                    wish to ignore altogether the Jews primarily because of the latter’s influence
                    in the United States. If the British accept the counterproposals the Arab
                    delegates hope to quickly win over the Grand Mufti of Palestine.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
